│ The issue is demonstrated with a small LLVM IR file. The transformation performed by `instcombine` is incorrect, as proven by Alive2.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The core of the issue lies in this transformation:                                                                                                                                       │
│ Original IR:                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```llvm                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ entry:                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   %add.ptr = getelementptr i8, ptr %ptr, i64 1                                                                                                                                           │
│   br label %for.cond                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ for.cond:                                                                                                                                                                                │
│   %.pn = phi ptr [ %add.ptr, %entry ], [ %incdec.ptr, %for.cond ]                                                                                                                        │
│   %val = load i8, ptr %.pn, align 1                                                                                                                                                      │
│   %cond = icmp ne i8 %val, 0                                                                                                                                                             │
│   %incdec.ptr = getelementptr inbounds nuw i8, ptr %.pn, i64 1                                                                                                                           │
│   br i1 %cond, label %for.cond, label %exit                                                                                                                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Transformed IR:                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```llvm                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ entry:                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│   br label %for.cond                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ for.cond:                                                                                                                                                                                │
│   %ptr.pn = phi ptr [ %ptr, %entry ], [ %.pn, %for.cond ]                                                                                                                                │
│   %.pn = getelementptr inbounds nuw i8, ptr %ptr.pn, i64 1                                                                                                                               │
│   %val = load i8, ptr %.pn, align 1                                                                                                                                                      │
│   ...                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformation tries to strength-reduce the pointer induction. It creates a new PHI node `%ptr.pn` for the base pointer of the `getelementptr`.                                      │
│ The problem is that the original code has two `getelementptr` instructions with different properties:                                                                                    │
│ 1. `%add.ptr = getelementptr i8, ptr %ptr, i64 1` (not `inbounds`)                                                                                                                       │
│ 2. `%incdec.ptr = getelementptr inbounds nuw i8, ptr %.pn, i64 1`                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The transformed code uses a single `getelementptr`:                                                                                                                                      │
│ `%.pn = getelementptr inbounds nuw i8, ptr %ptr.pn, i64 1`                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This new GEP inherits the `inbounds` and `nuw` flags from `%incdec.ptr`. However, on the first iteration, `%ptr.pn` is `%ptr`, and the GEP computes `ptr + 1`. The original GEP for this │
│ first step (`%add.ptr`) was *not* `inbounds`. By making the new GEP `inbounds`, the transformation illegally strengthens the instruction, leading to undefined behavior if `ptr` is at   │
│ the end of an allocation, as demonstrated by the Alive2 output.                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to ensure that when sinking multiple GEPs into a single one, the resulting GEP's flags are a conservative intersection of the original GEPs' flags. In this case, since one   │
│ GEP is `inbounds` and the other is not, the resulting GEP should not be `inbounds`.                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This logic is likely located in `InstCombine/InstCombinePHI.cpp`, where PHI-related optimizations are implemented. I will search for the code that performs this transformation and      │
│ correct the flag propagation.                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ A quick search points to `visitPHI` in `InstCombinePHI.cpp`. Inside, there's a section that handles induction variable simplification. The logic for combining GEPs seems to be around   │
│ where it calls `GetElementPtrInst::Create`. The flags for the new GEP are taken from one of the existing GEPs, which is incorrect.                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to compute the intersection of the flags. For `inbounds`, if any of the original GEPs is not `inbounds`, the new GEP cannot be `inbounds`. The same logic applies to other    │
│ flags like `nuw` and `nsw`.                                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify `InstCombine/InstCombinePHI.cpp` to correctly compute the flags for the newly created GEP instruction. I'll start by finding the relevant code block. The transformation   │
│ seems to be related to `visitIVUsers`, which is called from `visitPHI`. Inside `visitIVUsers`, there's a loop over PHI users, and one of the cases handles GEPs. The logic for creating  │
│ the new GEP is there. I will add code to intersect the flags.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                   │
